│ THOUGHT: The miscompile occurs when InstCombine canonicalizes a select-of-fcmp into maxnum/minnum, which unconditionally evaluates the operand and becomes poison with ninf when the     │
│ variable is -inf. Broadly disabling the transform for all ninf broke tests. To minimize impact, I will restrict the guard to the specific problematic case: when hasNoInfs is set and    │
│ one of the operands is a zero constant. That matches the reproducer (max(%in, 0)). I’ll add a check to skip creating maxnum/minnum if ninf is present and either operand is zero,        │
│ avoiding the miscompile while preserving other optimizations.                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ applypatch << 'EOF'                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ *** Begin Patch                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ *** Update File: llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp                                                                                                                   │
│ @@                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ -    if (SIFPOp->hasNoNaNs() && SIFPOp->hasNoSignedZeros()) {                                                                                                                            │
│ +    if (SIFPOp->hasNoNaNs() && SIFPOp->hasNoSignedZeros()) {                                                                                                                            │
│        Value *X, *Y;                                                                                                                                                                     │
│        if (match(&SI, m_OrdOrUnordFMax(m_Value(X), m_Value(Y)))) {                                                                                                                       │
│ +        // Avoid canonicalizing to maxnum when fast-math disallows infinities                                                                                                           │
│ +        // and one operand is zero. This can turn a previously guarded -inf                                                                                                             │
│ +        // (which would not be selected) into unconditional poison by evaluating                                                                                                        │
│ +        // the maxnum unconditionally.                                                                                                                                                  │
│ +        if (SIFPOp->hasNoInfs() &&                                                                                                                                                      │
│ +            (match(X, m_AnyZeroFP()) || match(Y, m_AnyZeroFP())))                                                                                                                       │
