│ THOUGHT: The failing test shows that InstCombine is still canonicalizing a select of FP values with fast-math including ninf into maxnum/minnum, which is more poisonous than the source │
│ when an operand is -inf. To fix this miscompile comprehensively, we should prevent the min/max canonicalization whenever the select has hasNoInfs set. I will add a simple early guard   │
│ in the min/max block: if SIFPOp->hasNoInfs(), return nullptr.                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '/if (SIFPOp->hasNoNaNs() && SIFPOp->hasNoSignedZeros()) {/a\      if (SIFPOp->hasNoInfs())\n        return nullptr;' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp       │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
